The paper discusses the design space for applying mobile touchscreen devices to programming situations, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and software engineering (SE) aspects. The paper also surveys previous work on programming-related tasks, which falls under programming languages (PL) and education (EDU) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges and opportunities for using mobile touchscreen devices in programming, which could relate to cybersecurity (CYBER) concerns.
